main event: Three unidentified flying objects were observed flying from North to South in Menomonee Falls, Wisconsin on 3/2/1964.
interesting points: The objects were seen for a duration of 40-60 seconds,The objects changed their relative positions during the observation,The observation was initially thought to be birds, but there was no strong light source to reflect from them,The case was regarded as UNIDENTIFIED, There were no photographs or physical evidence of the sighting.
witness description: Civilian observations, including Dr. Rudolph Walte and two girls who declared they saw the objects.
